## ğŸ”´ What â€œoverrideâ€ actually means

ğŸ‘‰ **Override only applies to methods**, not variables.

### Override happens when:

1. There is **inheritance**
2. Parent method is `virtual`
3. Child redefines the same method

Example:

```systemverilog
class A;
  virtual function void show();
    $display("A");
  endfunction
endclass

class B extends A;
  function void show();   // OVERRIDE
    $display("B");
  endfunction
endclass
```

âœ… This is override
âŒ Your case is NOT

---

## ğŸ”¹ Why your code works

Because of this rule:

> **Access control applies to where a variable is accessed, not who calls the function.**

So:

| Access           | Allowed? | Reason              |
| ---------------- | -------- | ------------------- |
| `a` inside class | âœ…        | local allows it     |
| `b` inside class | âœ…        | protected allows it |
| `pac.a`          | âŒ        | outside class       |
| `pac.b`          | âŒ        | outside class       |
| `pac.post()`     | âœ…        | public method       |

